# Axium Cursor Rules

- Source of truth: .github/copilot-instructions.md
- Keep routes in src/routes, handlers in src/handlers, models in src/models, SQL in src/database.
- Use AuthenticatedRouteBuilder for protected routes.
- Preserve RBAC vectors, validator-based validation, and utoipa annotations.
- Keep changes small and idiomatic to the existing Rust codebase.
- Commands: make app, make app-build, make migrate, cargo test, cargo clippy, cargo fmt.
- Pitfalls: SQLx macros need schema metadata; missing env vars can panic.
